The selection of deliciously prepared vegetarian and pescatarian dishes are simply plenty.  The Banana Boat is a self service buffet styled restaurant that offers more than ten different vegetable pans. The choices begin with freshly prepared and well seasoned rice and beans. As you continue walking, you will find long grain white rice, lemony herb couscous, spiced spinach, butter corn, sweet potatoes, black beans in gravy, string beans, southern styled collard greens and etcetera.  As impressive as the vegetable choices were, the freshly prepared fish choices were even more masterly magnificent.  As delicious as the food at the Banana Boat is, the restaurant absolutely does not deserve more than three stars because of the rude cashier.  After collecting my food, I walked to the counter that was simply too tall, placed my dish onto the formidable counter.  I was instructed by a young man engaged in conversation with a female, who had appeared from behind the cashier booth, to ring a bell. I rang the bell several times and then waited nearly five minutes. The cashier had appeared with the most wrathful scowl. During my rather brief encounter with the cashier, I was made to feel worthless and unwanted by the lack of eye contact and rude tone in the cashier's voice.  It is truly a shame that my experience was so damaged by the unprofessional cashier.  If you are willing to tolerate being treated like worthless rubbish, I would recommend you try the deliciously prepared dishes at the Banana Boat; the food is an absolute five star👏🏿
